00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:54,930
Dalton!

4
00:01:53,630 --> 00:01:54,930
Did you find him?!

5
00:01:54,930 --> 00:01:58,430
Here he is! We found Dalton!

6
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:01,330
What?! They found him?!

7
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,230
Thank goodness!

8
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:05,300
Dalton!

9
00:02:06,130 --> 00:02:07,360
Who is that, anyway?!

10
00:02:12,230 --> 00:02:13,400
This is terrible...

11
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:17,410
There's no heartbeat.

12
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:25,000
In order for you to get
a healthy smile back,

13
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,540
I prepared an exceptionally
nutritious dish.

14
00:02:28,540 --> 00:02:30,380
Thank you, Sanji.

15
00:02:30,730 --> 00:02:35,550
Despite what your body endured,
you're still so gorgeous that it hurts.

16
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:39,470
Good grief. Who said you could use
my kitchen without asking?

17
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:41,950
Madam, that roast over there is yours.

18
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:43,980
It's high in protein and will rejuvena–

19
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:46,470
I'm not a "madam."

20
00:02:46,470 --> 00:02:50,190
I may be single, but I'm
still beaming with beauty.

21
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:52,780
You're only 139 years old, right?

22
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:55,150
Doctorine! Help me!

23
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:58,420
Wait! Hey! Wait!

24
00:02:58,420 --> 00:03:00,340
Wait!

25
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:03,870
Wait! Wait!

26
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:05,750
What are you doing?

27
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:09,080
This guy's gonna join us
and become our friend!

28
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,020
Oh, really?!

29
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:12,920
I didn't agree to anything like that!

30
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:13,550
You did.

31
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:14,150
I didn't!

32
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:14,970
You did!

33
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:16,250
Be quiet, both of you!

34
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:19,430
Wait!

35
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,600
Friend, huh?

36
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:25,640
What a strong significance
that word holds for him.

37
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,400
You have no idea...

38
00:03:29,770 --> 00:03:36,050
When he was all alone, only one man
was able to open his heart.

39
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:39,520
His name was Dr. Hiriluk.

40
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:44,950
He was a quack who gave Chopper
his name and cared for him as a son.

41
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,920
Hold it!

42
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:53,430
Is he there?!

43
00:03:53,430 --> 00:03:55,070
No! We can't find him!

44
00:03:55,070 --> 00:03:57,500
Hiriluk, that darn quack!

45
00:03:57,500 --> 00:04:00,370
We'll catch him at all costs!
Those are King Wapol's orders!

46
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:01,380
Yes, sir!

47
00:04:13,550 --> 00:04:15,780
Dammit...

48
00:04:16,570 --> 00:04:20,240
You can't go on like this.
Let's call a doctor.

49
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,690
It's pointless. There aren't
any doctors in this country...

50
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:27,100
except for the Issie 20
who belong exclusively to Wapol.

51
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:31,230
Then we'll beg Wapol to let
the Issie 20 come here! I'll go.

52
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:33,820
There's no need for that.

53
00:04:38,780 --> 00:04:40,220
I'll examine him.

54
00:04:40,220 --> 00:04:43,850
Hiriluk! N-No thank you!
Please don't!

55
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:47,270
A bunch of people you treated
ended up getting worse!

56
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:49,140
Don't be nervous.

57
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:53,110
I just developed a wonderful
cure-all yesterday.

58
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:55,190
You're in luck.

59
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:02,230
Hm? It's not what you think.
That's just a tranquilizer gun.

60
00:05:02,230 --> 00:05:04,270
It's for patients in extreme pain.

61
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:06,480
I-I'll go and get the guards!

62
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:11,830
Please leave! If it's
money you want, I'll pay!

63
00:05:12,410 --> 00:05:17,180
I don't take money from sick people.
I just want to help you.

64
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:21,550
Don't! Stop it! I've got a family!

65
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:26,010
Croak! Ribbit! Croak! Ribbit!

66
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,980
Croak! Croak!

67
00:05:28,980 --> 00:05:32,430
Hm? This is strange.
Did I use the wrong ingredient?

68
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:37,820
I thought frog extract would work.
Damn... Guess it was a failure.

69
00:05:37,820 --> 00:05:39,870
S-Sorry... I didn't mean
for this to happen.

70
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,950
Hiriluk! Are you in there?!

71
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:44,870
Hold it!

72
00:05:49,570 --> 00:05:50,680
Hmm?

73
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:57,800
Are ya happy, young man?

74
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,520
The doctor hunt is almost over.

75
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:04,760
I hear that you and I are
the only doctors left in this country.

76
00:06:05,010 --> 00:06:08,520
Wapol is desperately trying
to catch us.

77
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,850
Even if he wasn't,
you're an outcast around here...

78
00:06:12,460 --> 00:06:15,230
seeing as you're nothing but a quack.

79
00:06:18,070 --> 00:06:21,620
I won't get caught
by some doctor hunt.

80
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:25,160
One day, I'll save this country
using medical science.

81
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:29,160
Oh? Didn't you mean to say
"destroy this country"?

82
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,080
There are people on the bridge!

83
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,050
I'll see you around, quack.

84
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:35,540
I'd like to avoid that, thief.

85
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:46,590
I'll never get caught!

86
00:06:46,590 --> 00:06:49,920
I'll save as many
sick people as possible!

87
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:52,060
Hm?

88
00:06:56,230 --> 00:06:57,810
You've been shot?

89
00:06:57,810 --> 00:07:00,730
We need to stop the bleeding
right away or you'll die!

90
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,400
Don't worry. I'll save you!

91
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:06,030
It's a yeti! Shoot it dead!

92
00:07:08,780 --> 00:07:12,450
I made a new ointment just three days ago
that heals broken bones.

93
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:13,830
You're in luck.

94
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,160
Don't let it get away!

95
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,420
Take it down!

96
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:22,380
Shoot it!

97
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:30,400
What are you?
You don't look like a human.

98
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:33,560
Oh, right, you're that yeti
everyone's been talking about.

99
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:48,380
Yeah! We hit it!

100
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:50,530
It wasn't enough! Finish it!

101
00:07:58,470 --> 00:08:02,460
H... How dare you...

102
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,460
Who do you...

103
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:08,430
think I am?!

104
00:08:08,430 --> 00:08:10,340
Hey! Wait!

105
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:17,040
I'm not going to shoot you!

106
00:08:18,790 --> 00:08:22,060
My name is Dr. Hiriluk!

107
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,690
I'm a doctor!

108
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:21,830
That was Chopper and Hiriluk's
first encounter.

109
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:27,960
So what happened
after Hiriluk took in the reindeer?

110
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:32,430
What?! You can talk?!

111
00:09:36,610 --> 00:09:39,440
Why didn't you say anything
for three days?

112
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:43,150
I thought you'd hate me if I talked.

113
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:47,480
When I talked to humans
the other day, they shot me...

114
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:50,280
because it's strange
for a reindeer to speak.

115
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,240
So what if you can speak?

116
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:58,240
I can speak, too.
A lot better than you can.

117
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,460
Run, Chopper!

118
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:03,420
What?

119
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:13,020
Dammit! It failed again!
Hey, are you okay, Chopper?!

120
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:20,220
Hmm? Well, you weren't okay
to start with, I guess.

121
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:27,940
Why are you calling me Chopper?

122
00:10:28,660 --> 00:10:30,990
You're Tony Tony Chopper.

123
00:10:30,990 --> 00:10:36,570
After all, you're a reindeer whose
first-rate antlers can chop down trees.

124
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:40,400
That's a cool name, isn't it?
That's what I'll call you.

125
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:44,060
Chopper...

126
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:52,630
Listen, Chopper. You must observe
patients carefully while treating them.

127
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:56,130
Doing so will save people's lives.

128
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:01,810
Let's go! With every passing day,
patients are depending on me!

